The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A sub-inspector and four constables of Ghughudanga outpost of Dum Dum police station on Dum Dum Road were injured on Monday when a group of local Trinamul Congress supporters who had gone to the outpost to lodge a complaint allegedly turned violent. The sub-inspector was admitted to RG Kar Hospital with head injuries. Some officers of Ghughudanga outpost were injured by hoodlums on Monday evening. We are looking for the culprits, said Rahul Srivastava, the superintendent of North 24-Parganas police. Local Trinamul Congress councillor Mriganka Bhattacharya denied that Trinamul men had attacked cops.     Four men were arrested at the airport on Sunday night on the charge of carrying rifle scopes without documents. Sarbinder Singh, Nitin Taluja, Satinderjit Singh and Randip Singh Sahani, all between 40 and 45 years old and residents of Delhi, arrived from Bangkok on a Kingfisher flight with 20 rifle scopes in their luggage. The scopes were detected during scan of the luggage. The four claimed that they did not know how the rifle scopes got into their luggage.     Some hoodlums carrying CPM flags allegedly forced their way into Indraprastha Apartment complex near Kaikhali on VIP Road on Monday and threatened residents with dire consequences for moving court to stop a construction that was encroaching on their premises. Residents lodged a police complaint alleging that the hoodlums kidnapped the liftman of complex.    Youths on a motorcycle snatched a bag containing Rs 25,000 from trader Joydev Mondal at Sonarpur on Monday afternoon. Police said Joydev, who deals in agricultural products, was going to make a payment when the incident occurred.    A 23-year-old youth was found hanging from the ceiling in his house on Dewangazi Road at Bally on Monday morning. Neighbours said Abhijit Majumdar had been suffering from depression because he was unable to find a job.     Residents of HB Town in Sodepur blocked the Sodepur-Madhyamgram road for about two hours on Monday morning protesting the scarcity of drinking water in the area. The blockade was lifted after municipal officials promised to improve water supply.     Bahar Ali was arrested in Tiljala late on Sunday on the charge of stealing cellphones in Salt Lake over the past few months. Two stolen cellphones were found on him. Ali was produced before the Salt Lake ACJM court on Monday and remanded in police custody for seven days.    Residents of Carry Road in Sheikhpara, Howrah, on Monday evening complained of oil leak from a petrol pump in the area. Police suspect the reservoir of the pump had sprung a leak.     Trinamul Congress supporters gheraoed the officer-in-charge of Barasat police station for about three hours on Monday evening to protest lax policing in the area. Sydul Islam, a Trinamul leader, was allegedly beaten up by hoodlums on Monday morning and had to be admitted to Barasat District Hospital.    A motorcycle was stolen from Elliot Road on Sunday night.            
